<h1>Problem 289 - 2014 EGMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(D\) and \(E\) be points in the interiors of sides \(AB\) and \(AC\), respectively, of a triangle \(ABC\), such that \(DB = BC = CE.\) Let the lines \(CD\) and \(BE\) meet at \(F.\) Prove that the incentre \(I\) of triangle \(ABC\), the orthocentre \(H\) of triangle \(DEF\) and the midpoint \(M\) of the arc \(BAC\) of the circumcircle of triangle \(ABC\) are collinear.</p>
